data.name: cb_CLIOnly.Text
data.value: This app formats command lines for bittwiste.exe and then runs it. It takes an input (or source) file and for every UDP packet that matches the IP and port entered in 'Input File' it will update those 4 fields with whatever is entered in the output file. It runs bittwiste twice: First time remaps the IP addresses, second time remaps the UDP port numbers. Even if you don't change all of the fields it will still run twice. It creates an intermediate file called TEMP.PCAP that you can delete. You probably need to run Wireshark on the source file to figure out the IPs and ports required under 'Input File'.
